Capital One Bank (USA), National Association: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 7:31 AM ET
Banks

Company Overview of Capital One Bank (USA), National Association



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Capital One Bank (USA), National Association offers financial products and services to consumers, small businesses, and commercial clients in the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom. It offers personal banking solutions, which include credit cards, checking accounts, savings accounts, and online and mobile banking tools; mortgages and home equity solutions, such as home loans and home equity lines of credit solutions; and auto financing home, new and used auto financing, and auto loan refinancing solutions. The company also provides business banking solutions, which include checking accounts, savings accounts, business credit cards, merchant services, and cash flow management servi...
Capital One Bank (USA), National Association offers financial products and services to consumers, small businesses, and commercial clients in the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom. It offers personal banking solutions, which include credit cards, checking accounts, savings accounts, and online and mobile banking tools; mortgages and home equity solutions, such as home loans and home equity lines of credit solutions; and auto financing home, new and used auto financing, and auto loan refinancing solutions. The company also provides business banking solutions, which include checking accounts, savings accounts, business credit cards, merchant services, and cash flow management services; and loans and lines of credit solutions, such as working capital lines of credit, equipment and vehicle loans, real estate term loans, business installment loans, and small business administration loans. In addition, it offers commercial banking solutions, such as commercial lending services, depository services, treasury management services, capital markets, and private banking and wealth management services for commercial and industrial, commercial real estate, energy, government banking and municipal finance, government contracting, healthcare, vacation ownership, not-for-profit, professional service, security, and technology sectors. Capital One Bank (USA), National Association was formerly known as Capital One Bank and changed its name to Capital One Bank (USA), National Association in March 2008. The company was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in McLean, Virginia. Capital One Bank (USA), National Association operates as a subsidiary of Capital One Financial Corporation.
Detailed Description


1680 Capital One DriveMcLean, VA 22102-3491United StatesFounded in 1994



